#PGML

BEGIN_PGML

It is the final point of an ultimate frisbee game and the disc has been thrown into the end-zone. One particular observer notices
that the disc rotates in such a way that its angular velocity can be modelled by the equation [`\vec\omega =`] [`[$coefficient_A]\theta\ \hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}`] 
where [`\theta`] is in radians. Find the time required for the disc to reach an angular velocity of [`\vec\omega =`] [`[$w_final]`] [`\hat{k}\ \textrm{rad/s}`] and its final displacement
if at time [`t = 0`] in seconds it starts at [`\theta = [$theta_initial]\pi\ \textrm{rad}`].


